  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the IDPs and overwhelmed communities in Idleb with fixed and mobile  health 
services interventions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In line with the strategic objective 1 of the HRP for Syria and the health cluster-specific objective 1 as well as the current allocation-specific objectives, HIHFAD seeks to Provide life-saving and life-sustaining humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable people with an emphasis on those in areas with high severity of needs.
through this project, HIHFAD will continue provision of health services via one PHC  located in Kalbbet /Alamal Camps with a population of 26,719 according to HeRAMS  95% of them are IDPs and to increase the accessibility of essential health services through a mobile unit and teams connected to the fixed PHC, the mobile unit will provide health services via qualified medical team and will continue visits to the camps in need based on weekly plans in coordination with IHD ( Idleb Health Directorate ) and the partners in the same area. In addition, in order to ensure the availability of specialized services to the most vulnerable people and persons with functional difficulties, 5 mobile teams will continue Home to home visits to support patients with physiotherapy treatment, mental health services and distribute assistive devices, also refer medical cases in coordination with Kalbeet PHC and Secondary health facilities

1 fixed PHC: provide women, children, people with NCD and elderly health services in addition to essential LAB services  ( PHC level 3 according to the EHSP essential health service package 
1 mobile unit: outreach patients in the camps and conducts health consultations 
5 mobile teams: conduct home/tent  visits and provide multi-sectoral service (physiotherapy sessions, MHPSS, material supports, referrals)</narrative>
  </description>
